        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 5:48AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 548 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 7 miles north of Clayton to 7 miles northwest of
Cleveland. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mountain City, Demorest, Lake Rabun, Mountain Rest, Long Creek,
Tallulah Falls, Batesville, Bad Creek, Pine Mountain, and
Turnerville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
